spanishExample: Si vamos a ese destino, vamos a ver a tu abuelita.
englishTranslation: If we go to that destination, we’re going to see your granny.

spanishExample: Estoy completamente de acuerdo contigo, pero él no desea nada para su cumpleaños.
englishTranslation: I completely agree with you, but he doesn’t wish for anything for his birthday.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué dices que obviamente no va a venir? Ha estado bien últimamente.
englishTranslation: Why are you saying that he’s obviously not coming? He’s been doing well lately.

spanishExample: Ojalá podamos estar aquí, pero obviamente él va a querer salir de casa.
englishTranslation: Hopefully we can be here, but obviously he’s going to want to get out of the house.

spanishExample: Ojalá pudiéramos ir al parque y a la plaza, pero no tenemos tiempo.
englishTranslation: I wish we could go to the park and the square, but we don’t have time.

spanishExample: Su amiguito vive cerca del puente.
englishTranslation: His little friend(dim) lives near the bridge.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué estás corriendo tan temprano últimamente?
englishTranslation: Why are you running so early lately?

spanishExample: Te prometo que definitivamente no haré eso en ese estado.
englishTranslation: I promise you that I definitely won’t do that in that state.

spanishExample: Estoy completamente listo, pero sé que habrá muchísimos problemas.
englishTranslation: I’m completely ready, but I know there will be a whole lot of problems.

spanishExample: ¿Has visto el primer piso? No nos gusta nada en ese sitio.
englishTranslation: Have you seen the first floor? We don’t like anything on that site.

spanishExample: Dicen que está en todas partes, aun entre los árboles.
englishTranslation: They say that it’s everywhere, even among the trees.

spanishExample: ¿Estás totalmente de acuerdo?
englishTranslation: Do you totally agree?

spanishExample: Siempre corre en esa dirección porque ahí está la entrada.
englishTranslation: He always runs in that direction because there is the entrance.

spanishExample: Aun sin auto, llegamos temprano a la casita.
englishTranslation: Even without a car, we arrived early at the little house(dim).

spanishExample: Iremos a la sala enseguida porque estamos absolutamente tristes.
englishTranslation: We’ll go to the living room right away because we’re absolutely sad.

spanishExample: ¿Me prometes que harás lo que yo desee?
englishTranslation: Do you promise me that you’ll do whatever I wish for?

spanishExample: ¡Corran! Van a llegar totalmente tarde y tendrán muchísimos problemas.
englishTranslation: (plural) Run! You’re going to arrive totally late and you’ll have a whole lot of problems.

spanishExample: Me habías prometido que lo harías enseguida.
englishTranslation: You had promised me that you would do it right away.

spanishExample: Ellos te desean lo mejor, así que ojalá puedas hacerlo.
englishTranslation: They wish you the best, so hopefully you’ll be able to do it.

spanishExample: Nos lo habías jurado, ¿por qué no estás en la salida todavía?
englishTranslation: You had sworn it to us, why are you not at the exit yet?

spanishExample: Me prometió otra cosa, pero esto es un infierno.
englishTranslation: He promised me something else, but this is hell.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué prometiste eso? Desearía que no lo hubieras hecho.
englishTranslation: Why did you promise that? I would wish you hadn’t done it.

spanishExample: Deseaba muchísimas cosas, pero eso fue definitivamente un error.
englishTranslation: I used to wish for a whole lot of things, but that was definitely a mistake.

spanishExample: Absolutamente, tienes que correr si quieres llegar a tiempo.
englishTranslation: Absolutely, you have to run if you want to arrive on time.
